Between 5th Avenue & East Drive, opposite 107th Street
{{Coord|40.7951434|-73.9529624|name=Fort Clinton (Central Park)}}

Fort Clinton was built during the War of 1812 as part of New York City's defenses, and was later demolished. A mortar (cannon barrel) was unearthed at the site in the early 1900s. Bosworth designed a pedestal for the mortar and a memorial plaque.
